    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "{\n  \"narration\": \"As you rise from your seat and gather your things, Cira the innkeeper catches your gaze from behind the bar. She wipes her hands on her apron and leans in with a thoughtful look. \\n\\n\\\"Elen, you say? She was in here just the night before she vanished,\\\" Cira recalls, her brow furrowing. \\\"Normally that girl keeps to herself, but she seemed restless, pacing by the hearth, checking her map over and over. Kept asking folk if anyone had heard howls near the shrine, or spotted strange lights out by the old boundary stones.\\\"\\n\\nCira lowers her voice, glancing at the other patrons. \\\"She was worried about the wards failing, you know. Said something about feeling watched even in daylight, and muttered that if she didn't come back, someone should warn Old Tommen. I didn't think much of it at the time--folk have been on edge. But now...\\\"\\n\\nShe shakes her head, concern etched in her features. \\\"If you're heading out after her, you might want to talk to Old Tommen yourself. He's usually by the square at this hour. And Norn, watch your back. The keep's shadow reaches further than it used to.\\\"\",\n  \"actions\": [\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updateTime\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"timeEstimate\": 5\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
