    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "{\n  \"narration\": \"Stepping out of the dense tangle of Gloamwood, you emerge into the Spectral Clearing. The air here feels unnaturally still, the hush broken only by the distant trickle of water and the low hum of magic that vibrates beneath your boots. Wisps of pale mist curl between the roots of ancient trees, and at the clearing's center stands a perfect ring of luminous mushrooms--the faerie circle, its glow subtly pulsing in time with your heartbeat.\\n\\nYou spot Elen's bootprints in the soft earth leading up to the edge of the mushroom ring, but they hesitate and double back, as if she sensed danger. The grass around the faerie circle is flattened in odd patterns, and the air is colder here, carrying a faint scent of wildflowers and ozone.\\n\\nAs you scan the clearing for signs of immediate trouble, a chill prickles at the back of your neck. Out of the corner of your eye, you glimpse a translucent, mournful figure drifting just beyond the circle--a ghostly presence, silent for now but clearly aware of your arrival. The specter's form shimmers, flickering in and out of view, its hollow eyes fixed on you.\\n\\nIf you wish to determine whether the ghost or the faerie circle pose a threat, or search for other dangers, you may attempt a Perception check. Roll a d20 and add your Perception modifier, then let me know the result.\",\n  \"actions\": [\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updateTime\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"timeEstimate\": 2\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
